<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="215" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/793: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Southern Baptist Mission
                                Board</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-02"><hi rend="italic">May 2,
                                1928</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department urges that you telegraph Dr. and Mrs. Gaston and Miss Cynthia
                            A. Miller at Laichowfu, Shantung Province, China, to withdraw as advised
                            by the American Consul at Chefoo from their station to Chefoo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>